 In a bid to meet its clients’ and customers’ needs, a hospitality company, Wells Carlton Hotels & Apartment, has launched an outdoor delivery through a digital medium. The digital food outlet, tagged the Wells Grill Takeout, is aimed at providing meals of international standard for customers. Sales Manager Jerry Opiughie said the services will meet the increasing demand for grill-based fastfood.  He said: “Through the Wells Grill Takeout, we want our customers to have the total experience when ordering from our digital platforms. We will in future expand our services to sell merchandise from pre-packaged sauces and T-shirt to potato cutters, all with our official brand attached to them in a bid to further build on this pop culture. “Our main focus will be serving high quality at a great value in a timely and hygienic process.”